HEADWORD: Gnash
<hw>Gnash</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To grind or strike the teeth
together.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There they him laid,⟦br⟧
<qex>Gnashing</qex> for anguish, and despite, and shame.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gnashingly</ent>⟦br⟧
